text: That's right, Javier, the increase of transport, collective, trains, will not only increase, well, now in January, as you know, within the numbers that were said, collective, minimum ticket, 77 pesos, trains, an increase of 45%, on rates that were very low, but also in the public audience, fixed for January 15, this is, of course, due to a publication today in the official bulletin of the Ministry of Infrastructure, of the Ministry of Transport, they are going to set a monthly increase formula, monthly, that is, collective and trains will increase every month, every month. Well, what is going to be done is, in the public audience, you remember that the public audiences are mandatory, but not binding, that is, you have to make a public audience before increasing the value of the tickets, although it is not binding, but what is going to be done in this audience, in the public audience, is to set a update formula. The last time this happened was in May of last year, at this point it is already January 3, 2023 is the last year, and there what was established in the public audience, which the truth is that, to be honest, they are almost always oriented, as it would be said in the university language, parodied by the national government in turn, at that time, in May, the formula that was chosen was the consumer price index, that is, the inflation of a month was known, and the next month the ticket increased in that proportion, I say, for you to see an example, for example, November was 12.7, when it was known in December, in January it would have increased that number, well, then it was suspended because of elections, because the price froze, what we already know.
